# Patient On-Boarding — Project Rules

## Architecture & scope

- Prefer simple, modular architecture.
- Do not add features outside the defined MVP.
- Before major refactors, explain the plan.
- After significant changes, summarize what changed and what remains.

## Frontend (React / Next.js)

- Keep components reusable and typed.
- Use TypeScript strictly.
- Use Tailwind utility classes cleanly.
- Prefer Server Components unless client state or browser APIs require a Client Component.
- Build mobile-first.
- Prioritize accessibility and readability.
- Avoid overdesigned SaaS patterns and AI-looking visuals.

## Forms & validation

- Use Zod for validation.
- Use React Hook Form for forms.

## Data & layering

- Keep API and service code separated from UI code.
- Never hardcode mock data inside UI components; use dedicated seed or mock files.

## Copy & tone

- Keep copy concise, clear, and healthcare-appropriate.
